main event: An unidentified bright light traveling exceedingly fast was observed over Indian House Lake, Canada, on 16 January 1949.
interesting points: The object emitted a bright light and was only observed as light, not the object itself., It was thought to be a shooting star or a meteor., No photographs were included in the report., The observation was made from the ground., The light traveled exceedingly fast according to the witnesses.
witness description: 1605 AACS Group personnel at Ft McAndrew, Newfoundland
